-- Rajat Gupta Judge Says He’s Inclined to Allow July 2008 Call
-- B y   P a t r i c i a   H u r t a d o
-- 2012-05-16T16:17:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-16/rajat-gupta-judge-says-he-s-inclined-to-allow-july-2008-call.html
The judge presiding over Rajat
Gupta’s trial for insider trading said he’s inclined to let
prosecutors introduce a secretly recorded July 2008 phone call.  On the call, Gupta discloses to Galleon Group co-founder
Raj Rajaratnam details of a  Goldman Sachs Group Inc. (GS)  board
meeting about the bank acquiring a commercial bank or  American
International Group Inc. (AIG)  U.S. District Judge Jed Rakoff in
Manhattan said that he will hear arguments from both sides
before making a final ruling.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patricia Hurtado in New York at 
 pathurtado@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Dunn at 
 adunn8@bloomberg.net  